Daily menu of an obese child: don't breakfast and dinner stuffed
Over one third of children aged 9 to 13 have overweight problems, where overweight affects 9% of the school population and obesity at 5%.
Obesity children come in most families with a lifestyle that is not healthy, according to current research.
The importance of the environment where it grows for a healthy development of the person, as well as the models that serve as a reference, is again demonstrated.
At the table, obese children, for example, feed on embites at least twice as often as children in families with normal weight.
For dinner, more than 19% of obese people had eaten fried potatoes the day before the analysis, which is linked to the prevention program "Obesity is not a coincidence".
In overweight families, there is no habit of practicing sports, which applies to most current families, where only 15 per cent of children responded that their parents, at least once a week, find time for physical exercise.
Survey of 900 children
The survey was conducted at the end of last school year and attended the same nearly 900 basic education children from all over Chechnya.
It was already the second edition of the program "The obesity of is not a coincidence", which supports the General Health Insurance Company and the Unilever company.
So far, more than 12,000 children have participated in the project from the 4th to the 8th course.
A proper diet and sufficient exercise in the family are determining factors, which significantly reduce the number of children with overweight and even obesity.
"Only half of the children polled have responded that they have five daily meals according to the regime: breakfast, lunch, lunch, lunch, lunch and dinner, which is one of the basic conditions for a healthy diet," says one of the results of the survey.
No breakfast but with lunch
Experts warn that, in a healthy development, details are important, as well, they also tell, such as having a fixed time for family breakfast.
In Chechnya, however, only 23 per cent of school families eat breakfast at the same time.
In most families, each one breakfasts alone.
But the worst thing was to find out that in 10% of the homes there was nothing breakfast.
Breakfast is, however, the basis of a correct daily diet.
The study shows that the families of obese children are more often consumed with fried potatoes.
Almost all - regardless of weight - drink daily sweet refreshments (70%).
Generally, more than 40 per cent of the children surveyed are sports, but among their parents this result is reduced to less than half, only 15 per cent.
Make your diet
The next phase of the study enabled the chosen boys (204 boys and 172 girls from 13 schools) to create their own diets from all possible offers according to their tastes and opinions.
"The food preferences of Czech children aged 12-15 years, from a healthy diet point of view, are far from ideal."
Among its favorite foods are pasta, meat and sweets
"The popularity of sweet refreshments is particularly alarming," the final report of the study states.
As the main food the palm is taken pasta and follows it closely with the poultry meat.
Practically, children always reject legume and taste for fish and vegetables is very low.
Change to Healthy Habits
At the same time, the study shows that children are willing to change their eating habits if they receive fair information.
"In the control group of the participants in the study, who filled out the questionnaire after the end of the prevention program "Obesity is not a coincidence", in many cases an important change was made in favour of the principles of healthy food," points out the results of the study.
It draws attention, for example, to sweet refreshments, where many children would begin to prefer normal and current water.
Children would also more often choose beef and fish for main food in the questionnaire and restrict the consumption of sweet food and flour products.
