Unlike the correct driving models, the same is no longer the case with collisions.
Of games of this kind you can't expect to recreate deformations and complicated collisions, but in fact before a blow against any object, you can't predict how your car will react, with which not everything is in order.
It is typical that, by making a very adjusted advance or circulating the car with a normal traffic, there are only slight rocks, but in other almost identical situations, your car ends up doing uncontrolled piruettes.
Or even completely destroyed.
Thanks to the reset system, there are no big problems, but it can put you in a bad mood.
The recipes are scheduled in such a way that when you suffer from an accident or get out of the track, the game will return you to the last rescue point on the track.
However, only five recipes are available in each race.
If you consume them all, you have to restart the race from the beginning.
So it's just a help in case something isn't right, but it's not very reliable.
Sometimes, neither reseteo helps, only helps him learn the given stage of memory.
A great disadvantage of the game is that the same facts are repeated in different places.
