Sometimes you'll find yourself in some "civile" vehicle site always with the same configuration, even if you're the first, fifth, or you're five minutes before or after.
This makes it anger especially in situations, when you see that two cars going to meet in opposite directions, your opponent advances without problems, but when you get there, you have to turn around or stop.
It's just like when you get there, because it's programmed that the "surprise" will always happen in front of your noses.
The opponents also have one more advantage.
During your departure you will arrive at places where, regardless of the time, you will always advance the same opponent on the same site.
Moreover, this happens at the end of the game, on a long bridge, which is even more shocking.
Your opponent must arrive before you, at any price.
When it goes in front of you, it makes it difficult for you to see the cars coming in front of you, so at first you can make the car butterfly.
You can understand the idea of creating a game with maximum doses of suspension and adrenaline, but the execution is so apparent that you are probably disappointed immediately.
And it's a shame, because even though the model of the trip is simple, the game is fun and with action, so it's often not possible to follow the detail what happens or where.
And it really does the same, if merit takes the idea with fifty exclusive clues or classification in the race so that it doesn't break the boredom, or anything else.
An unusual idea is the change of cars during the races.
You have to be aware of gas stationers next to the road, because right there you have to change cars, although in the vast majority of cases you will have enough of what you have.
The cars are divided into three categories.
Sports are suitable for urban areas, for strong American cars for straight highways and for super-deportive exotics for technical driving, for example, by mountain roads with curves.
In addition, the main narrative thread also appears a thread of parallel challenges, i.e., there are races in specific places that you will know by the stories.
Here you will get not only medals, but also points of experience for your profile, which serves both the challenges and the stories.
At the top level, the driver is opened up several possibilities, starting with the car and ending with funds for the profile.
At the same time, an Autolog feature is connected online, which compares your results with those of other players and provides other community functions.
One of the most difficult elements to understand is how the last race is made in history.
With the car you get to the metro tunnel (pass), where you run in the dark through the tracks (pass).
The Velocimeter marks you between 150 and 200 km/h (passe) and, suddenly, at the back comes the convoy of the metro and takes you forward without more.
In the writing we will probably have a discussion about this for several days, about whether during the programming of the game no one thought even a little or if the authors actually take us for a panda of fools.
The technical part of the game is nothing extraordinary, but at least the overall visual effects result in most nice cases, sometimes even superb.
What a pity that, at the most tense times, the quality of the image is reduced and, at times, in a serious way.
This mainly affects accidents where many participants are involved, when continuous image quality is no longer valid.
The audio is good and the soundtrack is a matter of taste.
In order to please most of the youth group, the soundtrack belongs to the category "each one of his father and mother", but it may be assumed that no one would buy the game just for his music.
The final feeling of Need for Speed: The Run is therefore quite confusing.
If the game were to avoid absolutely foolish mistakes, we would have trouble asserting that The Run is the best NFS game in recent years.
It gives the feeling that the game is not over.
Fun is secure, but be prepared because mistakes will hit you in the eyes with the strength of some airport reflectors.
The choirs of the University of Carolina will participate in the concert "Students of Terciopelo".
The joint celebration of the International Student Day and the anniversary of the Third World Revolution as a musical experience will take place for the third time at the Festa Academic Festival.
During the same period, twenty corals of high school and university centres will be presented.
The festival revolves around two concerts on November 17.
"The University of Carolina has a high participation in the festival."
Among the current choirs are the choir of the Faculty of Pedagogy and the Faculty of Humanities, in the festival committee is the rector Václav Hampl", said the head of the organization, Jakub Čaloun.
The summit of the entire festival is the free entrance to the high school choir concert, which will be held on 17 March at 14 hours in front of the National Technical Library in Dejvice.
The program includes the participation of the Czech jazzist Karel Ržička and his Celebration Jazz Mass.
At night will be held at the town halls in Vynohrady the concert "Tirciopelo Students", in which university choirs will participate, including the choir of the University of Carolina.
The Academic Festival aims not only to celebrate the International Student Day with dignity and to remember the 22nd anniversary of the Terciopelo Revolution, but also to present the choir music to the public at the highest level and to promote collaborative creation among young people.
The main organizer is the Czech Corals Union in collaboration with the Jan Kepler Secondary Institute.
All the acts were supported by the mayor of Prague, Bohuslav Svoboda, and the rector of the University of Carolina, Václav Hampl.
The Festival will take place between 16 and 20 November between Prague and Pardubice.
The calendar offers, in addition to the celebrations, a whole series of musical events, improvised shows of students and morning concerts.
Interested people will be able to find more information on the festival page www.festaacademica.cz
