Watson was so crucial to the company that, almost 40 years after taking up the chair of the boss, he was replaced by his son, Thomas Watson Junior.
Under its leadership, IBM began to work on the development of artificial intelligence and developed the first programming language.
In the 1960s IBM staff and computers helped NASA guide the flights to space (to Mercury, Saturn and in 1969 the famous flight to the Moon).
