Impact location.
The impact coordinates and the last record of the radar aircraft coincide, probably before the impact there was no loss of control or alteration in the flight path.
Dispersion of parts of the aircraft in a reduced area:
The information available so far allows us to assume that the impact occurred in a straight and side-by-side path.
The aircraft residue scatter pattern allows the helicopter to be assumed to have been impacted on the ground in structural integrity conditions.
No evidence of fire or explosion detected:
On the site of the sinister remains undiscovered in the remains of the ship of some kind of explosion or fire.
